49 hours into my water fast💦! Yes that means I only drink water! I have been doing this for years and the benefits are incredible! I love the app life because it shows you what is happening to your body during this process! I’m not encouraging anybody to water fast, (I’m not pretending to be a doctor) just sharing my journey because I love the benefits I experience!! I got really sick and have felt the most progress in healing just drinking water! Also the mental clarity is unreal✨ #enlightened anyone can do it because it’s free! 
✨If you feel like you need a bit of energy adding a pinch of salt and a bit of fresh lemon 🍋 to some water can give you those electrolytes and that boost you need!!
✨The book dopamine nation it has some good info on water fasting @duttonbooks 
✨ @dr.mindypelz has been a great resource for me with her knowledge - and she’s a doctor😉
Anyway, What questions do you have?? Or even better, who wants to join me on a water fast??
Xoxo

Woke up with the cramps from satan, a cut that won’t heal on my eyeball, and a couple of employees quit, feeling overwhelmed. And then my sweet friend Eric video chatted me after getting out of the hospital again asking for assistance with some medical bills and I melted. Perspective my loves🙏🏼 For those of you that have followed me for years you know his incredible story. I met Eric in Ghana years ago. He was hit by a bus and declared dead but didn’t die and continues to live with insane medical issues in a wheelchair. We went over his expenses and created a budget and plan. I want to send him money to cover his expenses for 2023 so he has everything covered for school, food, transportation for school, light and water paid for and his cell phone. I know everyone has so much going on in their own lives but if any of you feel like even sending a dollar I guarantee your life will be blessed in more ways than you give. Eric is such a light in the world and lives in the most humble conditions. We live in such a beautiful country and are so blessed. If you’re open or able to joining me in supporting Eric Venmo @hellodarlinglife and I will send every Penny over to him before the first of the year. Thanks again for always supporting the causes I am so passionate about. Love and light✨ xoxo 
#ghana #bekind #africa #giveback #dogood #donate #love #uplift #enlighten #journey #sharelove #thankyou #blessed #thisiswhatlifeisabout

“And it’s, it’s just we get so messy.
It’s not that we are doing lots of wrong things.
Our mind is so messy.
We don’t keep it simple.

Completely unnecessarily,
And it’s such a shame to end up feeling, in a real muddle
When actually, you ought to be having the time of your lives”

Love this beautiful reminder that when things feel overwhelming or complicated, or when my mind feels “messy”; I can simplify and get back to having the time of my life.

Hiiii hunnys. Time for a life update.✨ 
My fav compliment to receive is about my energy. It doesn’t matter what I look like, where I travel, people share the magnetism of my energy. My energy is just an outward currency of this inward work I have been doing aggressively for decades, and have been hyper focused on the last two! Growing up in an abusive home, I have healed (and will continue to heal) not only myself but generations of trauma through coaching, personal development courses, plant medicine, yoga, and meditation. Rather than keeping this magic for myself I am ready to share it with the world. Yes, I know most of you don’t even know a sliver of my story; and the story isn’t important. For those that do know me, I get asked often, “How have you created a life full of such magic and freedom, coming from so much pain???” I am here to share it with you. It is beyond time. Melissa, you can’t possibly know my exact pain, or what I’ve been through. I know my darling; and you don’t have to share anything you don’t want to. Pain is pain. And although it may have been created differently, the sweet healing of honey will drip where it needs to go and melt into your wounds. Part of my pain unfortunately has come from immense abuse and heartbreak. And I am here to tell you the upside is incredible. I would love to share how I have honed in on the sweet nectar of life with what has worked for me. Again, this is just my experience. Here is what has worked for me and we can use this as a starting point to find out what works for you. If any of this resonates with you even slightly, I challenge you to listen to that. If you feel even slightly lost, or are ready to make some major changes in your life I would love to support you. And no you don’t have to have experienced abuse or heartbreak to take this course; if you feel like you’re just stuck, if you want more from your life, Go to www.hellodarlinglife.com and click on the page “honeybee bodhi” to peep the details of what could be the biggest transformation of your life. Get ready to bee enlightened my lil honey bees 🍯🐝✨ #transformationcoaching #transformationcoach #enlightenment #makemagic #iseeyou #honeybeebodhi

Secrets out - I moved to Maui ✨🌈✨ Wild timing I tell you🙏 I heard about the fires while my shipping container was making its way across the ocean. So many emotions washed over me as I felt a bit guilty for having a home here that maybe others might need. I let myself feel it all, and sent lots of love over to these beautiful people. I also reminded myself I was following a dream, coming here to heal, and honoring what has been calling to me for a while😉 And that is the yin and yan of life. It’s complex. AND it’s also quite simple. It can be heartbreaking and joyful all at the same time. And as long as we honor all of it, we can always find the magic✨ On to new adventures and the next steps in my journey 🌈✨🌈 Can’t wait to share it with all of you lovelies😘🔥🌙 #maui #mauihawaii #hawaii #livingthedream #manifestation

While Machu Picchu and Rainbow Mountain get all the hype, we’re over here exploring the roads less-traveled (thanks to @intornocampers). We got several anonymous tips from the locals to check out Paracas National Reserve for sunset, so obviously we had to go. We drove the van to the tallest possible point we could get to and watched the sun fall below the horizon — it was worth it. ☀️

Hi lovelies - 44 hours into my water fast💦 Coming out from being in hiding and this big move had me feeling a little ungrounded and unsettled. Whenever I want clarity, and to really feel in my body, water fasting has been incredible for me. My experience of plant medicine is there is no avoiding things in my life, I get to take a serious look at everything that comes up. Water fasting for me is very similar, if not more powerful, and it’s free!! Instead of reaching out for food to comfort me or overworking myself, I get to sit with the emotion. If I actually sit with it and get curious, I can process it and let it go! So many shifts taking place for me and letting go of an old life that I am sooo beyond grateful for.🙏 And honoring the letting go has been so magical here in this beautiful jungle✨ No I’m not a doctor, I’m not telling you to stop eating and just drink water, I’m just sharing something that has been a powerful tool for me. If you read about it you can see the concept has historical significance, dating back to ancient civilizations and various cultural practices. Fasting has been embraced by many spiritual and religious traditions as a means to purify the mind and body, promoting self - discipline and contemplation🌙 Have you tried plant medicine or water fasting?? What was your experience of either/or both?? What questions do you have about it?? I would love to hear if anyone is open to sharing 🙏🤍🙏 xoxo

-1.5 cups of milk alternative

-2 teaspoons cinnamon powder

Top with 
- An apple Sautéd in butter or ghee and cinnamon
- Drizzle honey 🍯 to your hearts desire 🤍

Ghana 🇬🇭

Is it possible to have your heart break and be soooo full at the same time?? 😭💔😭 So hard leaving these beautiful children today to continue our journey.🇬🇭 I fell asleep and under a tree and woke up to them fanning me with leaves. 😭😭😭 They’re not at school because their parents don’t have any money for the school fees. Yet their love and tenderness could not come from any curriculum taught. The people and community here are the reason I continue to come back. The love here is unmatched by any other place in the world. 
There is so much struggle and pain here, yet more laughter and smiles than you see at any full stadium in America. Amidst the 100% humidity, lack of power and access to clean water, let alone medical care; this culture is just about love. So much to continually be thankful for. These kids are the best teachers. Happiness isn’t a mystery in Ghana 😍🇬🇭😍 #lifeisshortchangetheworld #africa #ghana #ghanastyle #danceparty #africa #africa #africa #africadanceparty #myfavs #dreamy #iloveyou #ghana🇬🇭

Every time I say this has been the hardest part of my life, I don’t think I’ve foreseen what was coming. These last four months have been the hardest of my life. I know we each have a sliver of the pie of what others are going through. I used to try and feed people the rest of my pie in hopes maybe they would see me, understand me better, or maybe have compassion for why I behave the way I do. What I’ve realized is it’s not my responsibility to do that. I’m so far from perfect, and im doing my best and to learn and grow every day. This trip with @hartafrica was so healing for me.🤍 Every time I go to Africa there are parts of my heart that fill up and expand, that I didn’t even know existed🤍 In Africa, amongst the cold showers, power outages, dirty hospitals and orphanages, undfed children, lack of food and education, excess of sweat and humidity; there is an abundance of smiles and sweet joy that I have yet to experience anywhere else in the world 🌎 What I’ve learned is pain is universal and so is love. My heart is fuller than I through possible, and I have received way more than I could ever give to these beautiful people. If you are struggling this holiday season - or ever; I invite you to do two things. One; do something for someone else, everyone has a need and if we open our eyes it won’t take long to see one we can fill. Two, figure out your WHY; so when the waves come crashing down, you are still standing. Thank you Africa for showing me that less is more, it’s the simple things that keep us happy, and that even without food and water and shelter there is something to be grateful for and smile about. And thank you  once again overflowing my soul with love and reminding me of my why so I can keep standing🌎🇬🇭🌎 #lifeisshortchangetheworld

When my beautiful friend asked me what my word is for 2024 the answer came so clearly. Instead of thinking of habits or things to take out of my life that I don’t want to be there, I’m adding more of what I do want✨ This feels so much yummier and juicier than stopping, shaming, not doing, restricting. It’s the language of increase 😉 And then the next part is not judge ourselves for whatever that want is. Maybe tonight you want to go to bed at 8pm, and tomorrow you want to stay out until 3 am🤪 And it’s all perfect. Taking away the pressure of doing all the things all the time feels so refreshing to me🙏 Maybe you’re already doing this, and I love that for you🔥 Just sharing where I am in my journey☀️My gift to myself is what to do I want more of now, in this moment, what does my body want?? When we take the time to ask ourselves, we will always get an answer. So wear the red dress, the red lipstick, and the high heels, or wear the sweatpants and stay in🤍 After going inward for so long and being alone I’ve noticed lately I am loving making magic again. What’s something you want MORE of today???? What are you gifting to yourself?? (Remember it will organically turn into weeks, months and years if we’re inviting it in today🌙) xoxo bbs😘
